30:51.000 --> 30:53.000
but we're like everybody else.

30:53.000 --> 30:55.000
And I think we wake up, a lot of administrators

30:55.000 --> 30:57.000
and leadership on campus wake up

30:57.000 --> 30:59.000
and ask themselves the same question every day

30:59.000 --> 31:01.000
when they look in the mirror.

31:01.000 --> 31:03.000
How do I increase my compensation

31:03.000 --> 31:05.000
while reducing my accountability?

31:05.000 --> 31:07.000
And we found the ultimate strategy.

31:07.000 --> 31:09.000
I called the LVMA strategy.

31:09.000 --> 31:12.000
When I went to UCLA, the facilities were shitty,

31:12.000 --> 31:15.000
but 76% got in and it was 400 bucks.

31:16.000 --> 31:18.000
And what they figured out is, I know,

31:18.000 --> 31:21.000
keep the admissions rates static and low.

31:21.000 --> 31:22.000
When the dean announces,

31:22.000 --> 31:25.000
we rejected 92% of our applicants this year at NYA,

31:25.000 --> 31:27.000
we stand up and we applaud.

31:27.000 --> 31:30.000
And the alumni love it because their degree goes up in value.

31:30.000 --> 31:33.000
And this same rejectionist LVMA strategy

31:33.000 --> 31:35.000
has been adopted across the larger economy.

