takes a real interest in new plans for new development,

31:44.000 --> 31:46.000
and they show up and they're very concerned

31:46.000 --> 31:48.000
and come up with thoughtful reasons

31:48.000 --> 31:50.000
why new developments never get the permits.

31:50.000 --> 31:53.000
And the result is we have a shortage every year

31:53.000 --> 31:57.000
of somewhere between 1.2 and 1.5 million houses we need.

31:57.000 --> 32:00.000
And then you have big companies who weaponize government

32:00.000 --> 32:03.000
and create it harder and harder for small companies to emerge.

32:03.000 --> 32:09.000
So the result is the incumbents see their asset values increase,

32:09.000 --> 32:12.000
but people can't get into these schools.

32:12.000 --> 32:15.000
Harvard sits on a $53 billion endowment,

32:15.000 --> 32:17.000
which is the GDP of Costa Rica,

32:17.000 --> 32:20.000
and it's kept its freshman class at 1,500 kids.

32:20.000 --> 32:23.000
A good Starbucks serves 1,500 people.

32:23.000 --> 32:27.000
They could admit 15,000 and have no tax,

32:27.000 --> 32:29.000
absolutely no tax on their resources.

32:29.000 --> 32:31.000
So one of the solutions in my view

32:31.000 --> 32:33.000
is if you are not growing your freshman enrollment

32:33.000 --> 32:35.000
faster than population growth,

32:35.000 --> 32:37.000
you should lose your nonprofit status.

